The official representative of the People’s Militia of the self-proclaimed Luhansk People’s Republic (LPR) Andrei Marochko said that in the winter of 2018-2019, Ukraine will send at least 3,000 new recruits to Donbass.
According to him, in this way, Kiev plans to "somehow complete the units".
"The unwillingness of Ukrainian citizens to serve in the ranks of the Armed Forces of Ukraine, mass dismissals led to a low staffing of the units," Marochko said, quoted by RIA Novosti.
He also did not rule out that the real numbers of Ukrainians called into the army can be increased if necessary.
In 2014-2017, Kiev began the so-called anti-terrorist operation (ATO), which was later replaced by the Joint Forces operation (JFO).
It was assumed that this measure would lead to a stronger role of Ukrainian security forces in resolving the situation.
At the end of August 2018, the situation in the Donbass worsened due to the assassination of the head of the DPR Alexander Zakharchenko.
The DPR authorities described the incident as a terrorist attack.
Several persons involved in the explosion were detained in the course of the criminal investigation.
According to preliminary data, they confirmed that the diversion was organized by Ukrainian intelligence services.
