In Indonesia after the earthquake more than 100 prisoners escaped from prison
More than 100 prisoners have escaped from a prison in the Indonesian province of Central Sulawesi.
Escape was made possible after two powerful earthquakes on the island of magnitude 7.2 and 7.4.
According to The Jakarta Post, the incident took place on September 28, when detainees in a prison in the city of Palu demanded their release due to underground thrusts.
More than 340 inmates staged a riot and set an institution on fire.
The police officers who arrived at the scene partially took control of the situation, but more than 100 people escaped from the prison.
The building itself has been seriously damaged, and the guards are hardly able to keep the prisoners.
The number of victims of the earthquake and tsunami that occurred on the island of Sulawesi increased to 832 people.
As a result, transport, electricity and communications with certain areas of the island are still not established.
"Golden Pearl" for "limited realism"
For the third time in history, the San Sebastián International Film Festival has recognized the Spanish film of the year as the best film of the year.
The main prize - "Golden Shell" - was awarded the drama "Between the Two Seas" directed by Isaac Lacuesta.
This film with almost documentary realism tells the difficult story of the lives of two brothers in the Spanish coastal province of Cadiz - Lacuesta presented the continuation of his 2006 painting "The Legend of Time".
At the award ceremony of the film festival in San Sebastián, the creators of the Argentine thriller "Red" were honored, which was marked immediately in several nominations.
Benjamin Naishtat was named Director of the Year, Pedro Sotero was awarded for his operatic work, and Dario Grandinetti was recognized as the best actor.
Actress of the year at the San Sebastian Film Festival was Pia Tjelta from Norway.
The jury praised her participation in the film "Blind Spot" - a drama about the life of one family after the attempted suicide of her daughter.
The film became the directorial debut of Swedish actress Tuva Novotna.
In the nomination "Best Screenplay" the victory was shared by the films "Yuli" and "The Faithful Man".
A special jury award was given to the Philippine crime drama Alpha: The Right to Murder.
Dizziness, tears and laughter
The festival in San Sebastián is called one of the main cultural events in Spain and one of the most important European film competitions.
About his impressions from the Euronews festival, the owner of the "Golden Shell" director Isaac Lacuesta told:
That was wonderful!
We came here with the whole team and of course we experienced dizzying moments, tears, laughter.
We're happy.
We started making this movie 14 years ago, it was a very long job, and what’s especially important to me is that we didn’t want to stop.
Now is the time for joy and gratitude.
According to Euronews correspondent Carlos Marlasca, the film of Isaac Lacuesta organically fit into the collection of paintings that received "Golden Shells", "but the festival in San Sebastián did not go without unexpected, sometimes shocking decisions of the jury, which sometimes even called the jury".
