Every resident of Kalmykia is a debtor.
Residents of the republic increasingly visit the official website of the Office of the Federal Service of Judicial Officers of Russia on the Republic of Kazakhstan.
According to the specialists of the department of organizational - control work, informatization and provision of information security of the republican department, over 140 thousand visits to the site itself have been registered for the past eight months, more than 42 thousand - section "Bank of data of executive productions", 661 payment receipts have been downloaded.
According to Valery Bogdanov, Chairman of the Public Council of the Russian Federal Security Service (UFSSP), almost every resident of the region is in debt for utility payments, fines, bank loans, loans, and no one is insured against unforeseen situations.
But debtors can expect negative consequences in the form of, for example, a ban on going abroad.
That is why the Russian Federal Security Service (UFSSP) recommends that all those who have planned a trip abroad clarify information about the presence of unpaid debts and repay them in the Department of Judicial Officers at the place of residence or on the website www.r08fssprus.ru.
The Service has created a "Data Bank of Executive Proceedings" for the convenience of citizens.
This special electronic application is available not only on the regional websites of the UFSSP of Russia, but also in social networks and mobile communication means iPad, iPhone and smartphone.
The database contains information about the executive proceedings initiated by the Kalmyk officers against all debtors, - explains the assistant head of the UFSSP of Russia on RC Delgir Bodgayev.
"In the presence of debts, the system provides information on the number and date of initiation of the executive proceedings; the name of the authority issuing the executive letter or other act; its number, amount and type of debt; the address of the department of bailiffs; FIO bailiff-executive; contact phone.
Information on the progress of the executive proceedings can also be obtained on the portal of public services at: http://epgu.gosuslugi.ru"
