The Ministry of Finance of the Russian Federation predicted the price of the ruble for 17 years ahead
The Russian Ministry of Finance expects a gradual weakening of the exchange rate of the ruble - to 73.9 rubles per dollar by 2031-2035, follows from the draft long-term budget forecast submitted to the State Duma together with the draft federal budget.
In 2021-2025, the rate of the ruble, according to the forecast, will be 66.4 rubles per dollar, in 2026-2030 - 71.1 rubles, and in the following five years - 73.9.
The Office notes that these figures are the nominal rate.
The real effective rate (indicator, taking into account the change in the exchange rates of the countries that are the main trading partners of the Russian Federation) will remain stable, officials assured.
As for inflation, it will be 3.5% by 2020, and then stabilizes at around 4%, according to the Ministry of Finance.
