Peskov responded to the question about possible support of Serbia for Kosovo
Russian Presidential spokesman Dmitry Peskov said it was premature to talk about whether Russia would provide assistance to Serbia after the escalation in Kosovo.
Negotiations should first be held between the leaders of the two countries.
The Kremlin spokesman told reporters of the radio station "Speaking Moscow" on Sunday, September 30.
On September 29, the resident of Serbia Alexander Vucic said that he intends to discuss the situation in Kosovo with the President of Russia Vladimir Putin at the next meeting in Moscow on October 2.
The Serbian leader also planned to ask Moscow for support in the current situation, clarifying that there is no military assistance in this case.
Vucic noted that he would like to preserve peace in the region and intends to do everything necessary for this.
Earlier that day it became known that the President of Serbia ordered to bring the armed forces of the country in a state of highest combat readiness.
